## Out of scope

*What this project explicitly will NOT do, even if technically feasible or adjacent. These are the most useful entries to write — they prevent scope creep before it starts.*

- <Out-of-scope item 1, e.g. "Custom dashboards. Ops teams use the existing BI tool for visualization; we only produce the data.">
- <Out-of-scope item 2, e.g. "External user access. The tool is internal-only; no per-customer logins.">
- <Out-of-scope item 3, e.g. "Real-time data. Daily refresh is acceptable; sub-hour SLAs are not on the roadmap.">

A change request that targets one of these items is not automatically rejected — but it forces the team to either re-scope (update this file) or decline (do not implement). Both are valid; silent drift is not.

